  "commentary": "**DEALER HEDGING COMMENTARY:**\n\nWith SPX at 6583.62 sitting between the massive negative gamma wall at 6500 (-4.5B) and positive gamma peak at 6600 (+3.6B), dealers are currently in buy-the-dip mode as we approach that key 6600 resistance where they'll flip to selling pressure. The PIN regime suggests dealers will aggressively defend both sides of this 6500-6600 range, creating a tight trading corridor with mean reversion bias. Watch for strong support building into 6500 where dealer buying accelerates, while any push toward 6600 should face increasing selling pressure from gamma hedging flows.\n\n**Bottom line:** expect price to ping-pong between 6500-6600 with dealers capping moves in both directions.",
